723955f-a.title: Manhattan: Wall Street - Front Street
723955f-a.text:
Wall Street, west from Front Street, showing mainly the south side
of same. Note the South Ferry division of the Second and Third Aves.
Elevated Lines on Pearl Street. At the S.W. corner of that point
appears the 25-storied triangular structure of the Munson Steamship
Line. Obscuring same is the 12-story Orient Building at the S.E.
corner of that point.
November 7, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
